<div1 type="letter">

<pb facs="nei.j4c.64.20" />

<fw type="curatorial">20</fw>

<opener>
<dateline>
5835 Vine Street<lb/>
Lincoln, Nebraska 68505<lb/>
November 15, 1972
</dateline>

<address>
<addrLine>Mr. Cyril Clemens</addrLine>
<addrLine>Editor, Mark Twain Journal</addrLine>
<addrLine>Kirkwood, Missouri 63122</addrLine>
</address>

<salute>Dear Cyril:</salute>
</opener>
<p>I thank you most heartily for the good things you say about my little book of memories. I especially appreciated what you said about Mark Twain sitting up to read it. Wouldn't that be something?</p>

<p>I am enclosing the Tom Sawyer First Day cover somewhat defaced by my signature and the address. I hope I haven't ruined it.</p>
<closer>
<salute>Kindest thoughts, as usual</salute>


<signed>John Neihardt</signed>


<note>JGN:nh</note>
</closer>

<postscript>
<opener>P. S.</opener> <p>May I show your letter to my publisher, Harcourt Brace Jovanovich?</p> <closer>&#8212; <signed><hi rend="caps">J. N.</hi></signed></closer>
</postscript>

</div1>
</body>

